@startuml Terminal Buffers - SRP Component Architecture

title Terminal Buffers - Single Responsibility Principle Design

package "SRP Buffer Architecture" {
    note as SRPNote
        SOLID Principle: Single Responsibility

        Each buffer has ONE job:
        - OutputBuffer: scrolling + buffering
        - InputBuffer: user input editing
        - CommandHistory: navigation
        - ThrobberAnimator: animation

        Benefits:
        - Independent testing
        - Clear separation of concerns
        - Easy to understand and modify
        - Composable in TerminalState

        Anti-pattern avoided:
        - NOT all in TerminalState
        - NOT God objects
        - NOT mixed concerns
    end note
}

package "OutputBuffer - Scrolling & Display" {
    class OutputBuffer {
        - buffer: Vec<String>
        - parsed_buffer: Vec<Line<'static>>
        - scroll_position: usize
        - visible_lines: usize
        - extra_lines: usize
        ---
        PUBLIC API:
        + add_line(line: String)
        + add_lines(lines: Vec<String>)
        + lines() -> &[String]
        + parsed_lines() -> &[Line]
        + visible_window(height) -> &[Line]
        + total_lines() -> usize
        + scroll_position() -> usize
        + scroll_up()
        + scroll_down()
        + scroll_to_end()
        + set_scroll_position(pos)
        + set_scroll_position_exact(pos)
        + is_at_bottom() -> bool
        + set_visible_lines(lines)
        + set_extra_lines(extra)
        + pop() -> Option<String>
        + clear()
        ---
        PRIVATE:
        - parse_ansi(line) -> Line
        - trim_if_needed()
        - auto_scroll_to_bottom()
        - total_content_lines()
    }

    note right of OutputBuffer
        Responsibilities:
        1. Store raw and parsed output
        2. Manage scroll position
        3. Calculate visible window
        4. Auto-scroll when appropriate
        5. Trim buffer (max 10K lines)

        Performance optimizations:
        - Caches parsed ANSI codes
        - No re-parsing on every render
        - O(1) window calculation
        - Lazy ANSI parsing (parse once)

        Smart auto-scroll:
        - Only auto-scroll if user at bottom
        - Preserves scroll position if scrolled up
        - Prevents jarring jumps

        Extra lines tracking:
        - Accounts for prompt + interaction
        - Updated by tui.rs during render
        - Accurate scroll calculations
    end note

    class Line {
        RATATUI TYPE
        Parsed text with styling
        Ready for immediate rendering
    }

    note right of Line
        From ratatui crate.
        Contains Span objects with
        text and style information.

        Pre-parsed so rendering
        doesn't need ANSI parsing.
    end note

    OutputBuffer --> Line : composes
}

package "InputBuffer - User Input" {
    class InputBuffer {
        - buffer: String
        - cursor_position: usize
        ---
        PUBLIC API:
        + insert_char(c: char)
        + delete_char()
        + move_cursor_left()
        + move_cursor_right()
        + clear()
        + set_text(text: String)
        + text() -> &str
        + cursor_position() -> usize
        + take() -> String
        ---
        PRIVATE:
        - char_to_byte_idx(char_idx) -> usize
    }

    note right of InputBuffer
        Responsibilities:
        1. Store current input text
        2. Track cursor position (in chars)
        3. Handle character insertion/deletion
        4. Support cursor navigation
        5. Provide text extraction

        Unicode safe:
        - cursor_position is in characters
        - Converts to byte indices internally
        - Handles multi-byte UTF-8 correctly

        Features:
        - Supports emoji (4 bytes per char)
        - Supports CJK (3 bytes per char)
        - Mixed ASCII and multi-byte

        Text operations:
        - insert_char: at cursor position
        - delete_char: backspace
        - take: extract and clear
        - set_text: from history/completion
    end note
}

package "CommandHistory - Navigation" {
    class CommandHistory {
        - history: Vec<String>
        - position: Option<usize>
        ---
        PUBLIC API:
        + add(command: String)
        + previous() -> Option<String>
        + next() -> Option<String>
        + reset_position()
        + all() -> &[String]
        ---
        PRIVATE:
        (None, just simple Vec and Option)
    }

    note right of CommandHistory
        Responsibilities:
        1. Store command history
        2. Navigate up/down with arrows
        3. Track navigation position
        4. Reset position on new input

        Behavior:
        - Skips empty/whitespace commands
        - position=None: showing new input
        - Arrow Up: previous() -> older cmd
        - Arrow Down: next() -> newer cmd
        - At end: next() returns None
        - Submit resets position

        Memory:
        - Unbounded (M1: no persistence)
        - All in memory during session
        - Lost on exit (M1 limitation)

        Edge cases:
        - Empty history: previous() returns None
        - Single entry: next() after is None
        - Rapid navigation: idempotent
    end note
}

package "ThrobberAnimator - Loading Animation" {
    class ThrobberAnimator {
        - index: Arc<AtomicUsize>
        - active: Arc<AtomicBool>
        - thread_handle: Mutex<Option<JoinHandle>>
        ---
        PUBLIC API:
        + new() -> Self
        + start()
        + stop()
        + is_running() -> bool
        + symbol() -> &'static str
        + frame_index() -> usize
        ---
        PRIVATE:
        (Uses atomic operations internally)
    }

    note right of ThrobberAnimator
        Responsibilities:
        1. Manage animation thread
        2. Cycle through braille symbols
        3. Provide current symbol on demand
        4. Handle start/stop gracefully

        Thread Safety:
        - All public methods thread-safe
        - Atomic operations (SeqCst)
        - Arc<> for shared ownership
        - Mutex for thread_handle

        Animation Details:
        - Dedicated thread (not blocking)
        - 100ms interval (10 FPS)
        - BRAILLE_DOUBLE symbol set
        - 4 symbols: ⠘ ⠙ ⠚ ⠒

        Idempotency:
        - start() safe to call repeatedly
        - stop() safe to call repeatedly
        - Drop trait ensures cleanup

        Returns:
        - symbol(): current braille or "~"
        - Used only in WaitingLLM mode
        - Called on every render
    end note
}

package "Composition in TerminalState" {
    class TerminalState {
        - output: OutputBuffer
        - input: InputBuffer
        - history: CommandHistory
        - mode: TerminalMode
        - pending_interaction: Option<PendingInteraction>
        - visible_lines: usize
        - multiline_buffer: Vec<String>
        - pending_heredoc: Option<String>
        - cached_prompt: String
        - throbber: ThrobberAnimator
        - is_root_mode: bool
        - scrollbar_info: Option<ScrollbarInfo>
        ---
        DELEGATION METHODS:
        + add_output(line: String)
        + clear_input()
        + submit_input() -> String
        + insert_char(c: char)
        + delete_char()
        + move_cursor_left()
        + move_cursor_right()
        + history_previous()
        + history_next()
        + scroll_up()
        + scroll_down()
        + scroll_to_end()
        ---
        MANAGEMENT METHODS:
        + get_prompt() -> String
        + refresh_prompt()
        + enter_root_mode()
        + start_throbber()
        + get_prompt_prefix() -> String
        + is_in_hitl_mode() -> bool
        + is_in_multiline_mode() -> bool
    }

    note right of TerminalState
        TerminalState is a COMPOSITE
        that delegates to focused components

        NOT a God object:
        - Doesn't duplicate responsibilities
        - Delegates to specialized buffers
        - Provides unified interface

        Composition benefits:
        - Each buffer independently testable
        - Clear concerns
        - Easy to mock for tests
        - Can reuse buffers separately

        Methods are thin wrappers:
        - add_output() -> output.add_line()
        - insert_char() -> input.insert_char()
        - history_previous() -> history.previous()
        - scroll_up() -> output.scroll_up()

        Management methods:
        - Prompt building/caching
        - Root mode tracking
        - Throbber control
        - Mode queries
        - Multiline state
    end note

    TerminalState --> OutputBuffer : contains
    TerminalState --> InputBuffer : contains
    TerminalState --> CommandHistory : contains
    TerminalState --> ThrobberAnimator : contains
}

package "Data Flow - Input to Output" {
    note as DataFlow
        INPUT FLOW:
        1. EventHandler.poll_event() -> TerminalEvent
        2. main.rs matches TerminalEvent
        3. Calls state methods: insert_char, etc
        4. InputBuffer updates internally

        HISTORY FLOW:
        1. User presses Enter
        2. state.submit_input() called
        3. InputBuffer.take() -> String
        4. CommandHistory.add(cmd)
        5. InputBuffer cleared

        NAVIGATION FLOW:
        1. User presses Up arrow
        2. main.rs calls state.history_previous()
        3. history.previous() returns Option<String>
        4. state.input.set_text(cmd)
        5. Prompt re-rendered with history cmd

        OUTPUT FLOW:
        1. Command executed (shell/LLM)
        2. main.rs calls state.add_output(line)
        3. OutputBuffer.add_line() parses ANSI
        4. Stores in parsed_buffer cache
        5. Auto-scrolls if user at bottom

        SCROLL FLOW:
        1. User presses PageUp
        2. main.rs calls state.scroll_up()
        3. OutputBuffer.scroll_up() moves position
        4. TerminalUI.render() called
        5. render_frame() uses new scroll position
        6. Scrollbar updated with new position

        RENDER FLOW:
        1. TerminalUI.render(state) called
        2. render_unified_content() called
        3. Gets parsed_lines from OutputBuffer
        4. Gets text from InputBuffer
        5. Calculates scroll from OutputBuffer
        6. Builds Paragraph widget
        7. Renders to frame with scroll offset
        8. Positions cursor on input line
    end note
}

package "Testing Strategy" {
    note as TestingBenefit
        SRP enables focused testing:

        OutputBuffer tests:
        - add_line, add_lines
        - scroll_up, scroll_down
        - auto_scroll behavior
        - trim when exceeds max
        - is_at_bottom detection
        - visible_window slicing

        InputBuffer tests:
        - insert/delete single char
        - cursor movement
        - Unicode (emoji, CJK)
        - take and clear
        - set_text positioning

        CommandHistory tests:
        - add and navigate
        - position tracking
        - next at end returns None
        - reset on submit

        ThrobberAnimator tests:
        - start/stop
        - idempotency
        - frame advancement
        - symbol cycling
        - thread safety

        Each tests component in isolation
        No mocking needed
        No dependencies between buffers
    end note
}

note bottom
    SOLID DESIGN PATTERNS APPLIED:

    S (Single Responsibility):
    Each buffer has one job

    O (Open/Closed):
    ThrobberAnimator can use different
    symbol sets without changes

    L (Liskov Substitution):
    Could replace buffers if needed

    I (Interface Segregation):
    Only expose needed methods per class

    D (Dependency Inversion):
    TerminalState depends on abstractions
    (public APIs), not implementations

    COMPOSITION OVER INHERITANCE:
    Buffers composed in TerminalState
    No deep inheritance hierarchies
end note

@enduml
